	   <tr><td colspan=2>A week ago, my level 15 cleric (also named Kyrsi, who has since been deleted) was wondering and poking about nro as I normally do with my Druid friend Alura (level 8 at the time, I was helping her kill spiders).<br>&nbsp;&nbsp; <br>I ran into a madman, who I've fought before, but never seen as a caster.  It was a druid.  Being cocky, I ended up going into the fight with very little mana, since I didn't realize it was a caster, and it conned green.<br>  <br>As the thing started to beat me to a bloody pulp, I told my friend to run.  As the madman knocked me down, a shriveled mummy came up, and attacked HIM, instead of me, oddly enough instead of frenzing on my body, the madman was distracted away, leaving me to bleed.  So I'm laying here with the lovely overhead camera, watching the madman (I really love how NPCs can cast to their heart's content.  Grr) pound the mummy into bandages.<br>  <br>The madman killed the mummy with the half health I had knocked it at, having conned green to me, and mummies generally conning stronger (I couldn't con this one as I was dieing), only to be jumped by a second mummy.  It was at this point that I died from bleeding.<br>  <br>It's too bad npcs that kill npcs don't leave corpses, cause when I came back to get my corpse, not a single mummy or madman was to be found anywhere nearby, and it was a short walk since I did bind in east FP.<br>  <br>Since that time, I've given up playing a cleric (I really hate sitting on my rear, watching the battle in the text window while I med to heal others), and started a druid.  Maybe I was envious that the madman druid could take out mummies better than a cleric could. =)<br>  <br>It's strange having Alura on a higher level than me now, heehee.<br>  <br>Moral of the story:  The overhead camera provides for some super exciting death footage!  Ohyeah, and madmen hurt.  Muchly.<br>&nbsp;<br>Kyrsi Kalasire<br>Druid of the 20th trampled twig<br>Zebuxoruk Server<br>Note to self: I am NOT a tank</td></tr>
