	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>There are 4 types of classes I have come across in my merciless extermination of madmen. <br><br>Wizard: They use a fire based damage shield (YOU are burned)And have no qualms using the 80DD spell of theirs (You convulse as lightning beams course through you). <br><br>Druid: These use a thorn damage shield (YOU are pierced by thorns) They will also use a wind spell that stuns you and a fire based DD that does about 11 damage. Grasping Roots is another that seems to take hold at the worse times (i.e Corpse retreival).<br><br>Monk: Not as dangerous as the casters. You know you are fighting a Monk if they Strike you or Block some of your hits.<br><br>Warrior: These are the most common madmen in Nro, they often spawn with a rusty or bronze sword of one type or another. <br><br>Note: Most of the casters are found near the Oasis side and if you watch them from afar they will buff themselves and so on. <br><br>Madmen drop lots of Water Flasks, gold coins, rusty and bronze weapons, and lower gems such as Bloodstones and Carnelians. They also have a habit of fighting mummies which is always fun to watch.<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
